    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 8500 - ADJUSTMENTS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ADJUSTMENTS</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
            <title>HOOD ADJUSTMENT AND ALIGNMENT</title>
            <para>The 8500 series front hood adjustment is done by moving the hinge plate attachment located at the
                front crossmember.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To adjust the hood left to right:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen the hinge attachment bolts and slide the hinge plate assemble left or
                        right.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Check the alignment with the hood contour lines. If the hood alignment is proper,
                        tighten the hinge plate bolts. Torque to 68 - 75 Nm (50 - 55 lbf-ft).
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To adjust hood forward and back (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900639">reference Figure 39</hotlnk>), loosen the hinge mounting bolts at the
                    mounting plate on the front cross member.
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Slide the hood forward or aft as required.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Check the distance between the rear edge of hood and clearance to windshield.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Tighten the hinge mounting bolts and torque to 68 - 75 Nm (50 - 55 lbf-ft).</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900639" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900639.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px" resolution="200"/>
                <caption>Figure 39. Hood Hinge Adjustment</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HINGE MOUNTING PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CHASSIS FRONT CROSSMEMBER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HOOD SUPPORT CROSS BAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. HINGE MOUNTING LOCATION ON CROSSBAR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
